== Lineages == === Mikumari-no-Kami Lineage === Mikumari-no-Kami, originally a [[water deity]] responsible for water distribution, came to be associated with child protection as the pronunciation of "Mikumari" (みくまり) shifted to "Mikomori" (御子守), meaning child protection. The head shrine of this lineage is {{ill|Yoshino Mikumari Shrine|ja|吉野水分神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Yoshino Mikumari Shrine|qq=}} in [[Yoshino, Nara|Yoshino, Nara]].
=== Kumano Hongū Taisha Lineage === The eighth shrine of Kumano Hongū Taisha, known as Komori-no-Miya, enshrines a deity referred to in the {{ill|Ryōjin Hishō|ja|梁塵秘抄|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ryōjin Hishō|qq=}}: "The children of the gods, such as the Wakamiya of Hachiman and the Wakōji and Komori Gozen of Kumano." Shrines in this lineage include the subsidiary {{ill|Kusu Shrine (Komori Shrine)|ja|楠神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Kusu Shrine (Komori Shrine)|qq=}} of {{ill|Fujishiro Ōji|lt=Fujishiro Ōji|lt=Fujishiro Shrine|ja|藤白神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Fujishiro Shrine|qq=}} in [[Kainan, Wakayama|Kainan, Wakayama]].
Additional associations include {{ill|Isagawa Shrine|ja|率川神社|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Isagawa Shrine|qq=}} in [[Nara, Nara|Nara City]], which is also known as Komori Myōjin.
